Global Ranibizumab Market Insights
Ranibizumab Market size was valued at USD 11.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 18.7 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Ranibizumab Market Overview
The global Ranibizumab market is valued at approximately USD 8.2 billion in 2024 and is projected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.1% from 2024 to 2032. Ranibizumab is primarily used for the treatment of retinal diseases like age-related macular degeneration (AMD) and diabetic macular edema (DME). The market growth is driven by rising prevalence of these conditions, increasing adoption of targeted therapies, and a growing geriatric population. Key market players such as Novartis and Roche continue to lead the industry, ensuring sustained innovation and availability of Ranibizumab worldwide. The demand for innovative, effective treatments has elevated the market value significantly, particularly in North America and Europe, with expanding access in emerging markets further contributing to growth.

